SIMPLE: open_door
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Open door
<hw>O"pen door</hw>. <sd>(a)</sd> <def>Open or free admission to all;
hospitable welcome; free opportunity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><q>She of the open soul and <qex>open door</qex>,⟦br⟧
With room about her hearth for all mankind.</q>
<rj><qau>Lowell.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sd>(b)</sd> <def>In modern diplomacy, opportunity for political and
commercial intercourse open to all upon equal terms, esp. with reference
to a nation whose policy is wholly or partially fixed by nations foreign
to itself, or to territory newly acquired by a conquering nation. <as>In
this sense, often used adjectively, as, <ex>open-door</ex> system,
<ex>open-door</ex> policy, etc.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><q>The steps taken by Britain to maintain the <qex>open door</qex>
have so far proved to be perfectly futile.</q> <rj><qau>A. R.
Colquhoun.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>open-ended</ent>⟦br⟧
